## Component Patterns

### Image Handling (MANDATORY)
- **ALWAYS** use `ImageWithFallback` instead of `<img>`
- Import: `import { ImageWithFallback } from "../components/figma/ImageWithFallback"`
- Usage:
```tsx
<ImageWithFallback
  src="https://example.com/image.jpg"
  alt="Description"
  className="w-full h-auto object-cover"
/>
```

### Navigation Links (MANDATORY)
- **Internal links**: Use Next.js `Link` component
- **External links**: Can use `<a>` with `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Pattern:
```tsx
import Link from "next/link";

<Link href="/about" className="...">
  About
</Link>
```

### Data Organization
- Define data arrays/objects at the top of component (before return)
- Use TypeScript types for complex data
- Example:
```tsx
export function MyComponent() {
  const items = [
    { id: 1, title: "Item 1", icon: SomeIcon },
    { id: 2, title: "Item 2", icon: AnotherIcon },
  ];
  
  return (
    <section>
      {items.map((item) => (
        <div key={item.id}>...</div>
      ))}
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Animation Classes
- Use classes from `styles/animations.css`:
  - `animate-blob` - floating blob animation
  - `animation-delay-2000` - delay 2s
  - `animation-delay-4000` - delay 4s
  - `fade-in-up` - fade in from bottom
  - `animate-gradient` - gradient animation
  - `animate-partner-marquee` - marquee animation
  - `animate-pulse-glow` - pulse glow effect

## Code Quality Rules

1. **No styled-jsx**: Use Tailwind CSS classes only
2. **Responsive Design**: Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
3. **Accessibility**: Include alt text for images, semantic HTML
4. **TypeScript**: Use proper types, avoid `any`
5. **Component Size**: Keep components focused, extract large sections
6. **Comments**: Use Vietnamese comments for business logic, English for technical

